label: Age range association
definition: A data transformation that translates a defined set of morphological changes relevant to ageing into a range of estimated age-at-death values.

label: Female age range association
definition: A data transformation that translates a morphological phase as defined by Brooks & Suchey observed on the pubic symphysis of a female specimen to the corresponding age range derived from regression analysis in Brooks & Suchey (1990).
definition source: Brooks, S., & Suchey, J. M. (1990). Skeletal age determination based on the os pubis: a comparison of the Acsádi- Nemeskéri and Suchey-Brooks methods. Human Evolution 5(3), 227-238 . doi:10.1007/BF02437238
